00053 static __inline ui32 hash_func(ui32 i)
00054 {
00055 #if QLZ_COMPRESSION_LEVEL == 2
00056         return ((i >> 9) ^ (i >> 13) ^ i) & (QLZ_HASH_VALUES - 1);
00057 #else
00058         return ((i >> 12) ^ i) & (QLZ_HASH_VALUES - 1);
00059 #endif
00060 }

00062 static __inline ui32 fast_read(void const *src, ui32 bytes)
00063 {
00064 #ifndef X86X64
00065         unsigned char *p = (unsigned char*)src;
00066         switch (bytes)
00067         {
00068                 case 4:
00069                         return(*p | *(p + 1) << 8 | *(p + 2) << 16 | *(p + 3) << 24);
00070                 case 3: 
00071                         return(*p | *(p + 1) << 8 | *(p + 2) << 16);
00072                 case 2:
00073                         return(*p | *(p + 1) << 8);
00074                 case 1: 
00075                         return(*p);
00076         }
00077         return 0;
00078 #else
00079         if (bytes >= 1 && bytes <= 4)
00080                 return *((ui32*)src);
00081         else
00082                 return 0;
00083 #endif
00084 }

00086 static __inline void fast_write(ui32 f, void *dst, size_t bytes)
00087 {
00088 #ifndef X86X64
00089         unsigned char *p = (unsigned char*)dst;
00090 
00091         switch (bytes)
00092         {
00093                 case 4: 
00094                         *p = (unsigned char)f;
00095                         *(p + 1) = (unsigned char)(f >> 8);
00096                         *(p + 2) = (unsigned char)(f >> 16);
00097                         *(p + 3) = (unsigned char)(f >> 24);
00098                         return;
00099                 case 3:
00100                         *p = (unsigned char)f;
00101                         *(p + 1) = (unsigned char)(f >> 8);
00102                         *(p + 2) = (unsigned char)(f >> 16);
00103                         return;
00104                 case 2:
00105                         *p = (unsigned char)f;
00106                         *(p + 1) = (unsigned char)(f >> 8);
00107                         return;
00108                 case 1:
00109                         *p = (unsigned char)f;
00110                         return;
00111         }
00112 #else
00113         switch (bytes)
00114         {
00115                 case 4: 
00116                         *((ui32*)dst) = f;
00117                         return;
00118                 case 3:
00119                         *((ui32*)dst) = f;
00120                         return;
00121                 case 2:
00122                         *((ui16 *)dst) = (ui16)f;
00123                         return;
00124                 case 1:
00125                         *((unsigned char*)dst) = (unsigned char)f;
00126                         return;
00127         }
00128 #endif
00129 }

00131 static __inline void memcpy_up(unsigned char *dst, const unsigned char *src, ui32 n)
00132 {
00133         // Caution if modifying memcpy_up! Overlap of dst and src must be special handled.
00134 #ifndef X86X64
00135         unsigned char *end = dst + n;
00136         while(dst < end)
00137         {
00138                 *dst = *src;
00139                 dst++;
00140                 src++;
00141         }
00142 #else
00143         ui32 f = 0;
00144         do
00145         {
00146                 *(ui32 *)(dst + f) = *(ui32 *)(src + f);
00147                 f += MINOFFSET + 1;
00148         }
00149         while (f < n);
00150 #endif
00151         }

00155 static __inline void update_hash(qlz_hash_decompress h[QLZ_HASH_VALUES], unsigned char counter[QLZ_HASH_VALUES], const unsigned char *s)
00156 {
00157 #if QLZ_COMPRESSION_LEVEL == 1
00158         ui32 hash, fetch;
00159         fetch = fast_read(s, 3);
00160         hash = hash_func(fetch);
00161         h[hash].offset[0] = s;
00162         counter[hash] = 1;
00163 #elif QLZ_COMPRESSION_LEVEL == 2
00164         ui32 hash, fetch;
00165         unsigned char c;
00166         fetch = fast_read(s, 3);
00167         hash = hash_func(fetch);
00168         c = counter[hash];
00169         h[hash].offset[c & (QLZ_POINTERS - 1)] = s;
00170         c++;
00171         counter[hash] = c;
00172 #endif
00173 }

00175 static void update_hash_upto(qlz_hash_decompress h[QLZ_HASH_VALUES], unsigned char counter[QLZ_HASH_VALUES], unsigned char **lh, const unsigned char *max)
00176 {
00177         while(*lh < max)
00178         {
00179                 (*lh)++;
00180                 update_hash(h, counter, *lh);

00705 #endif
